* Node Types & Cluster Size
** Instance Families
*** Memory-optimized (E-series)
****_ Large joins & aggregations
****_ High memory-to-core ratio
*** Compute-optimized (F-series)
****_ Complex CPU calculations
****_ Lower memory needs
*** Storage-optimized (L-series)
****_ Caching workloads
****_ Fast NVMe local disk
*** GPU-accelerated (NC/ND-series)
****_ ML / deep learning
****_ 10-100x faster than CPU
****_ Requires Databricks Runtime ML
****_ Photon must be disabled
** Worker config tradeoffs
*** Fewer, larger workers
****_ Less network shuffle traffic
****_ Good for analytical workloads
*** More, smaller workers
****_ Higher parallelism
****_ Good for batch processing
@endmindmap
